These files define which mobile applications are trusted to interact with your domain and can expose sensitive information such as internal or beta application identifiers, package names, certificate fingerprints, and URL paths, including potentially undocumented or staging routes. While this does not pose an immediate exploit, it increases the visibility of internal mobile assets and may aid reconnaissance by unauthorized parties. We recommend that your team review the current configuration, confirm whether all listed apps and paths are necessary for production, and remove any internal, beta, or overly broad entries to minimize unnecessary public exposure.
